Interface IJExpression

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IJGenerable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IJAssignmentTarget, IJExpressionStatement
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractJAnnotationValueOwned.FullClassNameExpr, AbstractJAnnotationValueOwned.JEnumConstantExpr, AbstractJExpressionAssignmentTargetImpl, AbstractJExpressionImpl, JArray, JArrayCompRef, JAssignment, JAtom, JAtomDouble, JAtomFloat, JAtomInt, JAtomLong, JCast, JEnumConstant, JEnumConstantRef, JFieldRef, JFieldVar, JInvocation, JLambda, JLambdaParam, JOpBinary, JOpTernary, JOpUnary, JOpUnaryTight, JStringLiteral, JVar

    public interface IJExpression
extends IJGenerable
    A Java expression.

    Unlike most of CodeModel, JExpressions are built bottom-up ( meaning you start from leaves and then gradually build complicated expressions by combining them.)

    IJExpression defines a series of composer methods, which returns a complicated expression (by often taking other IJExpressions as parameters. For example, you can build "5+2" by JExpr.lit(5).add(JExpr.lit(2))
